Comment (src/router/__tests__/index.spec.ts:20):
**Low — `.__name` is a Vue internal**

`__name` is set by the SFC compiler from the filename at build time. It works in Vitest today but it is not part of any public Vue API — it can be `undefined` under some bundler configurations (e.g. when `__name` is stripped by a minifier).

The preceding assertions (line 12: `route?.path`, line 13: `typeof component === 'function'`) already verify the route wires up the right file. Dropping the `__name` check removes fragility without losing coverage.
Implementation guidance: Update src/views/system-security-plans/SystemSecurityPlanCreateView.vue so the UUID field participates in native required validation. In the template, add required to the FormInput bound to systemSecurityPlan.uuid, alongside the existing v-model, class, and :disabled="isSubmitting" props. Do not change the payload shape or replace the generated UUID behavior; the field should still default to uuidv4() and remain editable/regeneratable when not submitting.
Implementation guidance: Update src/router/__tests__/index.spec.ts to stop asserting loadedComponent.default.__name. Keep the route lookup by name and the assertions that route?.path is '/system-security-plans/create' and route?.components?.default is a function. Remove the async component invocation, the loadedComponent variable, and the inline type that references __name; the test can be synchronous unless another public assertion is needed.
